		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Cumberland</placeName> <date>June 19<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1854</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. I. Leeser Esq</addressee>&#58;</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Dear sir&#58;  We <sic>belief</sic><lb/> it is interesting to you to hear some times some<lb/> thing about the <sic>wellfare</sic> &#38; improving con<lb/>dition of small congregations such as ours&#58;<lb/> it gives me pleasure to assure you that we<lb/> are spiritually &#38; <sic>finanzicaly</sic> prospering<lb/> <sic>thoug</sic> there may be some indifferent ones&#44;<lb/> the majority of our Cahl<add>&#63;</add> are good determined<lb/> Jews whom nought could induce to fall<lb/> back to the death like sleep of indifference.<lb/>  By Order of our President <persName>Mr S. Herdellerger</persName><lb/>&#44; elected may last.&#44; I am to inform you that our<lb/> Congregation is compelled to engage another<lb/> gentleman to fill the vacancy of Chasan Shochet<lb/> &#38; Teacher occasioned by the timely resignation of<lb/> <persName>Mr Wechsler</persName> our present functionary&#44; as also<lb/> to advertise in differen&#39;d papers we have<lb/> agreed with <persName>Mr W.</persName> that he will give up<lb/> the place at any time from the <date>first of August</date><lb/> or earlier otherwise continue his functions a<lb/> month after expiration of the Quarter being<lb/> to the <date>first of October</date> in case we are not able<lb/> to fill the vacancy sooner.  A single<lb/> man</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>man one of those generally emigrating from <placeName><sic>germany</sic></placeName><lb/> to this <sic>contry</sic> we prefer as expectation of such don&#39;t<lb/> overreact our ability&#44; we pay 250.00 doll.  you will<lb/> please to insert in the Occident a Notice in general<lb/> that on application to <persName>Frank</persName> &#38; <persName role="author">Adler</persName> further<lb/> particulars will be given&#44; and charge to the congregation<lb/> The accounts of the <sic>suffrings</sic> of our Brethren in<lb/> <placeName>Erez Israel</placeName> have reached us&#44; and <sic>dreadfull</sic><lb/> &#38; <sic>heartsickning</sic> <sic>the</sic> are indeed.  An Appeal made<lb/> to our brethren <sic>hier</sic> was heartily <sic>respondet</sic><lb/> to and from the result we are glad to send<lb/> to you&#44; the agent&#44; the enclosed Draft for 50 dol<lb/> on the western Bank of Balto. may this&#44; little as it<lb/> is&#44; contribute to alleviate such distress.</p>
				<p>we fail the monthly appearance of your Occident<lb/> and swarming as this <sic>country</sic> is with proselyte<lb/> scrip&#44; it cannot fail to refresh &#38; strengthen<lb/> the mind of every israelitish reader&#44; hoping<lb/> that you enjoy good health&#44; we take the<lb/> liberty to sign <sic>ourselfs</sic> your sincere friend</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">Henry Adler</persName></p>
				<p>Secty of the <add>&#63;</add> B. L Congregation</p>
		</body>
